<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[835,1474,1681,1736]" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,987,1681,1705]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Description. –</emphasis>
Larva: Body length 3.5-5.0 mm. Cerci length 
<quantity box="[835,965,1713,1736]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="1.3">1.3-1.7 mm</quantity>
. General coloration brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[835,1475,1777,2088]" lastBlockId="2.[136,775,193,344]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Head capsule brown, with off-white or cream areas between antennal bases and at base of labrum. Antennae slightly longer than length of head capsule; scapes pale, pedicels and flagella pale brown. Labrum (
<figureCitation box="[1148,1207,1873,1896]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[113,158,1978,1999]" captionTargetBox="[243,1339,220,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-106@1.[220,1348,204,1920]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1-16. Chopralla fusina, new species, larva and adult. 1. Labrum; 2. Left mandible, dorsal view; 3. Right mandible, dorsal view; 4. Left maxilla; 5. Labium (left: dorsal; right: ventral); 6. Gills 1 (top), 3, 5 and 7 (bottom); 7. Larval abdominal sterna III-V; 8. Legs of larva, pro- (top), meso-, metathoracic (bottom); 9. Paraproct; 10. Posterior margin of larval abdominal tergum III; 11. Posterior margin of larval tergum VII; 12. Posterior margin of larval tergum IX; 13. Right half of larval metanotum; 14. Foreleg of male adult; 15. Forewing of male adult; 16. Genital forceps." pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.4 times wider than long, clearly cleft anteromedially, with dorsal submedial pair of long, robust setae and anterior submarginal row of 4 long, robust setae. Incisors of left mandible (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[113,158,1978,1999]" captionTargetBox="[243,1339,220,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-106@1.[220,1348,204,1920]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1-16. Chopralla fusina, new species, larva and adult. 1. Labrum; 2. Left mandible, dorsal view; 3. Right mandible, dorsal view; 4. Left maxilla; 5. Labium (left: dorsal; right: ventral); 6. Gills 1 (top), 3, 5 and 7 (bottom); 7. Larval abdominal sterna III-V; 8. Legs of larva, pro- (top), meso-, metathoracic (bottom); 9. Paraproct; 10. Posterior margin of larval abdominal tergum III; 11. Posterior margin of larval tergum VII; 12. Posterior margin of larval tergum IX; 13. Right half of larval metanotum; 14. Foreleg of male adult; 15. Forewing of male adult; 16. Genital forceps." pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) with 6-7 denticles, and with stout, blunt triangular thumb. Incisors of right mandible (
<figureCitation box="[1134,1199,2033,2056]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[113,158,1978,1999]" captionTargetBox="[243,1339,220,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-106@1.[220,1348,204,1920]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1-16. Chopralla fusina, new species, larva and adult. 1. Labrum; 2. Left mandible, dorsal view; 3. Right mandible, dorsal view; 4. Left maxilla; 5. Labium (left: dorsal; right: ventral); 6. Gills 1 (top), 3, 5 and 7 (bottom); 7. Larval abdominal sterna III-V; 8. Legs of larva, pro- (top), meso-, metathoracic (bottom); 9. Paraproct; 10. Posterior margin of larval abdominal tergum III; 11. Posterior margin of larval tergum VII; 12. Posterior margin of larval tergum IX; 13. Right half of larval metanotum; 14. Foreleg of male adult; 15. Forewing of male adult; 16. Genital forceps." pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) separated apically, with 6 (3+3) denticles. Maxillary palps 2 segmented and subequal to galealaciniae in length (
<figureCitation box="[435,505,193,216]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[113,158,1978,1999]" captionTargetBox="[243,1339,220,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-106@1.[220,1348,204,1920]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1-16. Chopralla fusina, new species, larva and adult. 1. Labrum; 2. Left mandible, dorsal view; 3. Right mandible, dorsal view; 4. Left maxilla; 5. Labium (left: dorsal; right: ventral); 6. Gills 1 (top), 3, 5 and 7 (bottom); 7. Larval abdominal sterna III-V; 8. Legs of larva, pro- (top), meso-, metathoracic (bottom); 9. Paraproct; 10. Posterior margin of larval abdominal tergum III; 11. Posterior margin of larval tergum VII; 12. Posterior margin of larval tergum IX; 13. Right half of larval metanotum; 14. Foreleg of male adult; 15. Forewing of male adult; 16. Genital forceps." pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Labium (
<figureCitation box="[640,708,193,216]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[113,158,1978,1999]" captionTargetBox="[243,1339,220,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-106@1.[220,1348,204,1920]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1-16. Chopralla fusina, new species, larva and adult. 1. Labrum; 2. Left mandible, dorsal view; 3. Right mandible, dorsal view; 4. Left maxilla; 5. Labium (left: dorsal; right: ventral); 6. Gills 1 (top), 3, 5 and 7 (bottom); 7. Larval abdominal sterna III-V; 8. Legs of larva, pro- (top), meso-, metathoracic (bottom); 9. Paraproct; 10. Posterior margin of larval abdominal tergum III; 11. Posterior margin of larval tergum VII; 12. Posterior margin of larval tergum IX; 13. Right half of larval metanotum; 14. Foreleg of male adult; 15. Forewing of male adult; 16. Genital forceps." pageId="2" pageNumber="19">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) with glossae subequal to paraglossae in length; glossae with 10- 11 long, stout inner marginal setae; paraglossae with 6-7 ventral submarginal setae; labial palps 3 segmented, segment II with 2 long, robust dorsal setae apicomedially.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="1" pageNumber="18" startId="1.[113,158,1978,1999]" targetBox="[243,1339,220,1895]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[113,1452,1978,2114]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
Figs. 1-16. 
<taxonomicName authority="Tong &amp; Dudgeon, 2003" authorityName="Tong &amp; Dudgeon" authorityYear="2003" box="[235,403,1978,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Chopralla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusina" status="new species">
